 section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Intervention-Model"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Further we assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}$
\end_inset

 is completely independent of 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{pr}$
\end_inset

, but 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{2}$
\end_inset

 is correlated with 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{pr}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
x_{1=}\sigma_{trunc}\left(0,1\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
x_{pr}=[0,1]
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For generating our artificial population, we draw 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}$
\end_inset

