 In order to make the different scenarios better comparable, we constrain
 the absolute values in such a way that the geometric mean of all 4 entries
 must be the same in all scenarios.
 The geometric mean is the mean function usually used for variables related
 to growth-rates or similar.
 We set it to 
\begin_inset Formula $1/50$
\end_inset

.
